name: Help with one month's rent
description: ETL is a nonprofit organization, a 501 c 3 under the IRS. Donations can be tax deductable. As with all grassroots organizations, sustainability is always a balancing act. Our services include providing opportunities for youth and young adults who live with disabilities and/or special needs to learn life and work skills! We have gone on Urban Hikes to Boston, MA, Philadelphia, PA, and , Portland, ME…to name a few! Team building, communication, and independent living skills are amongst those reinforced with Urban Hike activities. ETL also provides peer to peer mentoring, Life Skills Trips (we’ve even gone to Old Quebec on these trips!), community based activities, and many other great opportunities!

name: Assist with student activities for one month.
description: Your help will assist us in providing services.  Whether it be a group activity, a trip to Boston on the train, going to Coos Canyon to pan for gold, or even a pizza party for a group of students, your funds help to continue activities for our youth and young adults!

name: Help with insurances for a month!
description: Organizational insurances add up! ETL carries three types of insurances, totalling over 500.00 per month. Donating to help specifically with the insurances will help tremendously!

name: Help with administrative costs
description: Our operating budget provides that the largest amount of funds spent goes toward direct services for our youth and young adults.  But, the reality is that we still need to carry on as a business and pay salary, pay utilities, and buy supplies!  Your contribution will help keep ‘business as usual’!  Our tax id number is 11-3674348.

name: Keep our van rolling!
description: ETL has a 15 passenger van to help with student transportation, trips, and monthly runs to fill the van for our food program. As you know, gas is really expensive! ETL serves many rural areas, so we rack up the miles! Please help with your generous donation! Thank you!
